[{"id":"VR598307","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram. In the diagram, the center of a pulley is attached to a horizontal ceiling above. A string passes over the pulley, with two unknown masses suspended from either end of the string. The mass on the left side of the string is labeled M sub 1 and the mass on the right side of the string is labeled M sub 2. Mass M sub 1 hangs lower than mass M sub 2.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR598307.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two objects of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 1\"><math alttext=\"M sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> are connected by a string that passes over a pulley with negligible mass and negligible friction, as shown. A group of students wants to use this setup to measure the acceleration due to gravity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following procedures could the students use?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR598307_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use equal masses, collect velocity data for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and calculate its acceleration.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use equal masses, collect position data for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and calculate its average velocity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use unequal masses, collect velocity data for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and calculate its acceleration.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use unequal masses, collect position data for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and calculate its average velocity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use different sets of equal masses, collect velocity data for each value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and calculate the average acceleration.</p>"],"answer":2}]